<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF346A8BFD1A9C201C0AB716" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF346A8BFD1A9C201C0AB716" blockId="207.[741,1335,2602,3029]" lastBlockId="207.[128,1334,3036,3463]" pageId="207" pageNumber="969">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFC809C201DD0B1A8" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[892,976,2681,2714]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFC199C201A5FB1A8" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[997,1119,2681,2714]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">horsfieldii</taxonomicName>
species group. See 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFCDC9CF91DC9B1F3" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[800,969,2720,2753]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">M. horsfieldii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFC249CF91AA1B1F3" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[984,1185,2720,2753]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adversus">Myotis adversus</taxonomicName>
previously included specimens that are now recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFC9B9CB71A35B03D" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" box="[871,1077,2798,2831]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moluccarum">M. moluccarum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFB799CB71B30B03D" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1157,1328,2798,2831]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">M. macropus</taxonomicName>
. Records attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFBE49D4F1AB4B005" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1048,1204,2838,2871]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adversus">M. adversus</taxonomicName>
in northern 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF346A8BFCDF9D671D9BB06D" box="[803,923,2878,2911]" name="Vietnam" pageId="207" pageNumber="969">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
were dubiously assigned to it and are tentatively considered to represent 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFCD59DD41DD4B09C" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[809,980,2957,2990]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">M. horsfieldii</taxonomicName>
. Subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFB7A9DD41B19B09C" authorityName="Arnback-Christie Linde" authorityYear="1908" box="[1158,1305,2957,2990]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">taiwanensis</taxonomicName>
is now considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF346A8BFB5A9DED1EA8B0CF" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fimbriatus">M. fimbriatus</taxonomicName>
, although some earlier molecular studies suggested that it was a distinct species. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
